Head.
Antenna with 34 flagellomeres; first flagellomere 1.35Ã— longer than second flagellomere. Face (
Fig. 84E
) strongly granulose. Clypeus (
Fig. 84E
) mat, slightly convex, apical margin slightly curved. Malar space granulose, 0.6Ã— basal width of mandible. Mandible with lamella. Frons granulose, median carina absent. Vertex granulose. Interocellar distance (
Fig. 84F
) 1.45Ã— ocello-ocular distance and 2.0Ã— distance between median and lateral ocelli. Temple nearly smooth, subpolished. Occipital carina evenly arched, reaching hypostomal carina at mandible base.

Mesosoma.
Pronotum granulose dorsally, trans-striate below. Mesoscutum (
Fig. 84G
) granulose. Scutellum granulose with posterior rugose. Metanotum rugose-punctate. Mesopleuron (
Fig. 84B
) granulose-punctate, transstriate below tegula, speculum smooth and shiny. Metapleuron (
Fig. 84B
) granulose with sparse and minute punctures. Propodeum (
Fig. 84C
) with anterior transverse carina close to base; area superomedia granulose; area petiolaris trans-striate; area superomedia confluent with area petiolaris, slightly depressed medially; all carina strong; propodeal spiracle small and oval.

Metasoma.
First metasomal segment (
Fig. 84H
) round in cross-section of basal 0.3, with weak dorso-lateral carina and a shallow lateral groove. Postpetiole and second tergite granulose. Second tergite 0.73Ã— as long as first tergite, 1.7Ã— longer than its apical width; thyridium oval, small, its distance from basal margin of tergite 3.0Ã— its length. Third tergite 1.1Ã— longer than its apical width. Sixth and seventh tergites without emarginations medially. Ovipositor sheath approx. 2.0Ã— longer than hind femur, ovipositor (
Fig. 84D
) gradually upcurved.

